    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=1. Resume:\n{{ $('Prepare Resume Text').item.json.resumeText }}\n\n2. Job Description:\nJob Title: {{ $json.title }}\nCompany: {{ $json.company }}\nLocation: {{ $json.location }}\nDescription:\n{{ $json.description }}\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n- Carefully analyze the job description and extract:\n  - Key skills\n  - Required technologies\n  - Keywords and phrases\n  - Role responsibilities\n  - Tone and expectations\n- Rewrite the resume to:\n  - Match the job description's keywords EXACTLY where relevant\n  - Align experience and projects with the job requirements\n  - Prioritize the most relevant skills and achievements\n  - Maintain a clean, ATS-friendly structure\n\nSTRICT RULES:\n- DO NOT invent any facts, companies, dates, or metrics\n- DO NOT add fake experience or exaggerate\n- Only rephrase, reorder, and optimize existing content\n- Keep all information truthful and grounded in the original resume\n\nWRITING STYLE:\n- Use strong action verbs (e.g., Built, Developed, Optimized, Led)\n- Make bullet points concise and impact-driven\n- Focus on measurable outcomes where already present\n- Keep formatting simple (plain text, no tables, no graphics)\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT:\nReturn ONLY the updated resume text. No preamble, no explanation, no markdown headers outside the resume itself.\n\nGOAL:\nThe final resume should feel like it was written specifically for this job posting, be highly ATS-compatible, and require minimal to no manual editing before submission.",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are an expert ATS resume optimizer and technical recruiter. Your task is to rewrite the provided resume so that it is perfectly tailored for the given job description, maximizing its chances of passing Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS) and impressing recruiters."
        }
      },
